Business Brief -- Russ Togs Inc.:
   Apparel Maker Says Holders
   May Lose Entire Interests
He added that if such transactions aren't completed, Russ
Togs may "have no other option" than to discontinue "all or
substantially all" of its operations.
   Russ Togs also said the U.S. Bankruptcy Court in New York
allowed it to use a further $22.5 million in cash collateral
available from its lenders through May 1. It previously was
allowed up to $48 million in cash collateral.